summary: Did you hear about that person that said, "Jonsa will never work due to a thing called the Westermarck effect. Since they lived...
question: Did you hear about that person that said, "Jonsa will never work due to a thing called the Westermarck effect. Since they lived like brother and sister as kids, there's just no sexual attraction."? I want to hear your thoughts on this.
answer:
I did nonny, I did. I saw it yesterday on twitter and ended up rambling on a little bit. lol This person also wrote another tweet under the original tweet, saying that Dracarys and Jon fell in love and were immediately attracted to each other due to GSA (genetic sexual attraction). And she said something like, “the attraction between them was inevitable because they share blood, look alike and are alike”, I just saw that op has deleted that second tweet tho. I mentioned it, because in my replies below, I do brush over what she said in that tweet a little.

So yeah.. psychology is all nice and dandy, but you gotta take into account many factors when you’re applying a theory, because in Jon and Sansa’s case the traumas they both went through opened a door that led them to, even if involuntarily, develop feelings for each other. 

So yeah, as I’ve said above, everyone lives different lives, has different experiences, everyone’s different, everyone’s minds/mentalities are different, we all think differently, so yeah.. you can’t just apply a psychology theory generally/to everyone, it doesn’t work like that lol

So yeah, these were my thoughts on that tweet nonny.

Thank you for the ask. 😚💙

summary: In a world where the gender roles are switched; men are expected to marry great ladies and women are sent to the wall or go by...
body:
In a world where the gender roles are switched; men are expected to marry great ladies and women are sent to the wall or go by choice, never to mother a child. Viscerys Targaryen has to fight off his oppressive sister and protect his unborn child in Droga, only to learn his daughter is a stillborn when trying to save Droga’s life.
When Anetta Stark is killed for supposed treason, the Stark family and the Lannisters declare war on eachother. Aryn and Saeyn Stark, the only two boys Anetta had, are rumored to be held captive. Anetta’s bastard daughter Joni is fighting at the Wall. Riana and Bevvy Stark are the only Starks left in Winterfell when Sani goes to fight the Lannisters with his aunt in tow, and captures Jennilyn Lannister, resulting in a long journey for the middle child and the loss of Jenny’s hand.
